<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 1:37PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Tuscola
and northwestern Lapeer Counties through 245 PM EDT...
At 137 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Davison, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Columbiaville and Otter Lake around 155 PM EDT.
North Branch around 220 PM EDT.
Clifford around 230 PM EDT.
Other locations impacted by this storm include Silverwood, Elba and
Fostoria.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
